<subSubSection id="2129F39EC45F21D5FC0B1CB2335C13B8" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="5932B8E8071051AAEFCA040ECE0A3702" pageNumber="35">
Diagnosis. The genus is distinguished from all other Bythitinae as defined by Cohen and Nielsen (1978) by the following combination of characters: Dwarf species reaching only 45 mm SL (
<taxonomicName id="DDE31C84251C22AE84AA86141E9BEB2C" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:3662C4A7-C2F3-4148-A660-D8573C286A49" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bythitidae" genus="Microbrotula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Microbrotula rubra Gosline 1953:219" order="Ophidiiformes" pageNumber="35" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rubra">M. rubra</taxonomicName>
). Body relatively short, head length 25.7-29.2% SL. Vertebrae 11-13 + 33-44 = 44-56. Dorsal fin retrograde, its origin above vertebrae 7-11, anal-fin origin beneath vertebrae 14-17. Neural spines of vertebrae 4-8 depressed; spine of first vertebra much reduced. Eye small, 6.5-17.5% HL. Anterior nostril with slight tube, located just above upper lip. Rear portion of maxilla ensheathed in 
<taxonomicName id="E7493836E2B8C2CE4066C71A2C216FD5" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:DC91DAF6-1D7B-40C6-A759-DF0254E15067" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bythitidae" genus="Microbrotula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Microbrotula bentleyi Anderson 2005:36" order="Ophidiiformes" pageNumber="35" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bentleyi">M. bentleyi</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="32A60124B867EA2170BD2CA97FCB2671" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:58194D2A-C6C8-4930-AD32-58F30D23DD4F" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bythitidae" genus="Microbrotula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Microbrotula polyactis Anderson 2005:38" order="Ophidiiformes" pageNumber="35" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="polyactis">M. polyactis</taxonomicName>
, free in remaining species, and with small, ventrally-directed projection at lower rear corner. Tongue with short, anterior projection, rounded at tip. Vomerine teeth in two small patches; palatine teeth viliform, in single row. Opercular spine strong, usually imbedded. Developed gill rakers 2-4, with tiny denticles on outer surface. Branchiostegal rays 7. Scales very small, imbricated, present on top of head and cheeks in adults. Lateral line mediolateral, of tiny papillae. Pectoral-fin rays 9-17, set on short peduncle that is higher than long. Pelvic fin of a single ray, its length growth-related but reaching almost to anus in adults. Caudal-fin rays 4-6 except in 
<taxonomicName id="F9DEEC2C8C7A15840F9FB15F954DA38E" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:58194D2A-C6C8-4930-AD32-58F30D23DD4F" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bythitidae" genus="Microbrotula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Microbrotula polyactis Anderson 2005:38" order="Ophidiiformes" pageNumber="35" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="polyactis">M. polyactis</taxonomicName>
which has 7-8 rays. Male intromittent organ simple, without ossified or sclerified parts (pseudoclasper).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
